one garlic bread
2 mini half-baked rolls
1 small camembert 145g
half a pink-lady apple
~130g pineapple (fresh but tinned probably works)

peel the apple & chop the fruit fairly small

pre-heat the oven to gas 6
heat on medium-high for 5 min, mash in the pan, and leave for another 3 min

cut the camembert open horizontally and put the bottom into a small terracotta dish
put the hot fruit on top (any that won't fit can stay in the pan to serve)
add the other half of the camembert on top

turn the oven up to gas 7
put the camembert dish in on the middle shelf
after 5 min, put in the garlic bread and mini rolls (mini rolls to the coller side of the oven if possible)
leave for another 15min

reheat any remaining fruit to serve, along with a bit of butter for the mini roll

